<subsection xml:id="subsec-application-of-scale-drawings1">
    <title>Application of scale drawings(1)</title>
    <p>
        <m>\textbf{Recall:}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        In the previous section, you made scale drawings. Check on how you did it and use to solve any question that 
        pops under scale drawing.
    </p>
    <p>
        In this section, you will apply scale drawing to determine actual measurements when given 
        scale measurements.
    </p>
    <activity>
        <p>
            <m>\textbf{Work in groups}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>What you require:</m> A piece of string and a ruler.
        </p>
        <p>
            <ol marker="(i).">
                <li>
                    <p>
                        The figure below shows the Map of Kenya showing <m>47</m> counties. Study it
                    </p>
                    <image source="/Kenya.png" width="70%">
                      <shortdescription>Map of Kenya</shortdescription>
                    </image>
                    <p>
                        The scale is given by <m>1:10\,000\,km</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Use the scale and the string to deteemine:
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <ol marker="a.">
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    The distance from Mombasa to Malindi.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    The distance from Wajir to Garisa.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    The distance from Hola to Lamu.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Discuss your work with other learners in class.
                    </p>
                </li>
                
                
                    
            </ol>
        </p>
        
    </activity>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                The scale of the map of a certain country is <m>1\,cm \,\text{represent}\,100\,m</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Write this scale in ratio form.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            The distance between a cattle dip and a homestadead on a map is 
                            <m>14\,cm</m>. Determine the actual distance between the homestade and cattle dip in kilometres.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            The scale in ratio form is given by:
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>1:100</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Distance between cattle dip and homestade <m>=14\,cm</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            First, you calculate the actual distance in <m>m</m> then finally convert to kilometres using,
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>1\,000\,m=1\,km</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <md>
                                <mrow>\textbf{If} \,1\,cm=\amp 100\,m </mrow>
                                <mrow> 14\,cm=\amp ?</mrow>
                                <mrow> =\amp \frac{14\,cm \times 100\,m}{1\,cm}</mrow>
                                <mrow>= \amp {\color{blue} 1\,400 \,m}</mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Convert <m>{\color{blue} 1\,400 \,m}</m> to kilometres.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            We know that;
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <md>
                                <mrow> 1\,000\,m=\amp 1\,km </mrow>
                                <mrow> {\color{blue} 1\,400 \,m}=\amp ?</mrow>
                                <mrow> =\amp \frac{1\,400\,m \times 1\,km}{1\,000\,cm}</mrow>
                                <mrow>= \amp 1.4 \,km</mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Therefore,
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Ditance between homestade and cattle dip <m>={\color{black} 1.4 \,km}</m>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
